 \"just seven events\", \"from\": 568, \"to\": 585}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 595, \"to\": 598}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among the lunch guests were relatives of Jack Beresford, who won the single sculls, and of the four men who triumphed in the coxless fours, Maxwell Eley, James MacNabb, Robert Erskine Morrison and Terence Sanders, Also present were descendants of Hugh \\\"Peter\\\" Dulley and Stephen Fairbairne, who were in the GB eight, and Vincent Boveington, who was in the coxed four.\", \"from\": 601, \"to\": 969, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 642, \"end\": 656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Beresford\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jack Beresford\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Beresford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Beresford\"}, {\"begin\": 741, \"end\": 753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maxwell_Eley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Maxwell Eley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maxwell_Eley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maxwell_Eley\"}, {\"begin\": 755, \"end\": 760, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_VI_and_I\", \"score\": 0.9999999787078198, \"rank\": 2.1292307644688977e-08, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_VI_and_I\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_VI_and_I\"}, {\"begin\": 770, \"end\": 784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Erskine\", \"score\": 0.9997733462503503, \"rank\": 0.0002267051333588154, \"text\": \"Robert Erskine\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Erskine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Erskine\"}, {\"begin\": 798, \"end\": 805, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Terence_Stamp\", \"score\": 0.9999860020572864, \"rank\": 1.3138890178176067e-05, \"text\": \"Terence\", \