edals\", \"from\": 992, \"to\": 998}, {\"ngram\": \"their ancestors\", \"from\": 1006, \"to\": 1021}, {\"ngram\": \"other mementoes\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1041}, {\"ngram\": \"crew photographs\", \"from\": 1051, \"to\": 1067}, {\"ngram\": \"their relatives' experiences\", \"from\": 1101, \"to\": 1129}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Steve O'Connor, director of the River & Rowing Museum, brought the gold medal won by Beresford, who was the most decorated Olympic rower until Sir Steve Redgrave surpassed his record more than 60 years later.\", \"from\": 1131, \"to\": 1339, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1131, \"end\": 1145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_O'Connor\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Steve O'Connor\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_O'Connor\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_O'Connor\"}, {\"begin\": 1163, \"end\": 1184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_and_Rowing_Museum\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River & Rowing Museum\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_and_Rowing_Museum\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_and_Rowing_Museum\"}, {\"begin\": 1274, \"end\": 1292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Redgrave\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sir Steve Redgrave\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Redgrave\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Redgrave\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"director\", \"from\": 1147, \"to\": 1155}, {\"ngram\": \"the gold medal\", \"from\": 1194, \"to\": 1208}, {\"ngram\": \"Beresford\", \"from\": 1216, \"to\": 1225}, {\"ngram\": \"the most decorated Olympic rower\", \"from\": 1235, \"to\": 1267}, {\"ngram\": \"his record\", \"from\": 1303, \"to\": 1313}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dr Treharne Jones, who had spent five months tracking down the families, said: \\\"It was wonderful to see so many people come together as strangers yet sharing the common thread of being descended from Olympians.\", \"from\": 1341, \"to\": 1551, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Dr Treharne Jones\", \"from\": 1341, \"to\": 1358}, {\"ngram\": \"five months\", \"from\": 1374, \"to\": 1385}, {\"ngram\": \"the families\", \"from\": 1400, \"to\": 1412}, {\"ngram\": \"so many people\", \"from\": 1445, \"to\": 1459}, {\"ngram\": \"strangers\", \"from\": 1477, \"to\": 1486}, {\"ngram\": \"the common thread\", \"from\": 1499, \"to\": 1516}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympians\", \"from\": 1541, \"to\": 1550}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Everyone enjoyed the occasion and the opportunity to bring their family memorabilia to a place where the men could be properly recognised and admired.\\\"\", \"from\": 1553, \"to\": 1705, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Everyone\", \"from\": 1554, \"to\": 1562}, {\"ngram\": \"the occasion\", \"from\": 1571, \"to\": 1583}, {\"ngram\": \"the opportunity\", \"from\": 1588, \"to\": 1603}, {\"ngram\": \"their family memorabilia\", \"from\": 1613, \"to\": 1637}, {\"ngram\": \"a place\", \"from\": 1641, \"to\": 1648}, {\"ngram\": \"the men\", \"from\": 1655, \"to\": 1662}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jamie Macnab, the grandson of James Macnabb, who died in 1990, said: \\\"It's wonderful that Robert invited us to learn a bit more about the crew.\", \"from\": 1707, \"to\": 1850, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1737, \"end\": 1750, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_MacNabb\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"James Macnabb\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_MacNabb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_MacNabb\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Jamie Macnab\", \"from\": 1707, \"to\": 1719}, {\"ngram\": \"the grandson\", \"from\": 1721, \"to\": 1733}, {\"ngram\": \"Robert\", \"from\": 1797, \"to\": 1803}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 1812, \"to\": 1814}, {\"ngram\": \"the crew\", \"from\": 1841, \"to\": 1849}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are going around looking for more evidence of Grandpa here at Leander.\", \"from\": 1852, \"to\": 1926, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1902, \"end\": 1909, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grandparent\", \"score\": 0.9999984492631684, \"rank\": 1.5507394031223371e-06, \"text\": \"Grandpa\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grandparent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grandparent\"}, {\"begin\": 1918, \"end\": 1925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leander_Club\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3961053545210658e-42, \"text\": \"Leander\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leander_Club\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leander_Club\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more evidence\", \"from\": 1885, \"to\": 1898}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's also about the event because this istheHenley rowing club.\", \"from\": 1927, \"to\": 1990, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 1943, \"to\": 1952}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If you love sport, to be invited to lunch here is an honour.\", \"from\": 1991, \"to\": 2051, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 2003, \"to\": 2008}, {\"ngram\": \"lunch\", \"from\": 2027, \"to\": 2032}, {\"ngram\": \"an honour\", \"from\": 2041, \"to\": 2050}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Grandpa was a member of the club and I understand that after the war he was involved in committee but the club was in financial difficulty and needed a lot of work to keep it going.\", \"from\": 2053, \"to\": 2235, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2054, \"end\": 2061, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grandparent\", \"score\": 0.9999984492631684, \"rank\": 1.5507394031223371e-06, \"text\": \"Grandpa\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grandparent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grandparent\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a member\", \"from\": 2066, \"to\": 2074}, {\"ngram\": \"the club\", \"from\": 2078, \"to\": 2086}, {\"ngram\": \"the war\", \"from\": 2115, \"to\": 2122}, {\"ngram\": \"committee\", \"from\": 2142, \"to\": 2151}, {\"ngram\": \"the club\", \"from\": 2156, \"to\": 2164}, {\"ngram\": \"financial difficulty\", \"from\": 2172, \"to\": 2192}, {\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 2204, \"to\": 2209}, {\"ngram\": \"work\", \"from\": 2213, \"to\": 2217}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Winning a medal at the Olympics wasn't such a big thing then but it was in later life when he got asked to events.\", \"from\": 2237, \"to\": 2352, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a medal\", \"from\": 2246, \"to\": 2253}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2257, \"to\": 2269}, {\"ngram\": \"such a big thing\", \"from\": 2277, \"to\": 2293}, {\"ngram\": \"later life\", \"from\": 2313, \"to\": 2323}, {\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 2345, \"to\": 2351}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He loved the attention.\", \"from\": 2353, \"to\": 2376, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the attention\", \"from\": 2362, \"to\": 2375}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He was a marvellous man who was very charismatic.\\\"\", \"from\": 2378, \"to\": 2429, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a marvellous man\", \"from\": 2386, \"to\": 2402}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mr Macnab, from Edinburgh, and his family will attend the Olympic regatta in Paris next week.\", \"from\": 2431, \"to\": 2524, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2447, \"end\": 2456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edinburgh\", \"score\": 0.9999904774470921, \"rank\": 9.522643487366434e-06, \"text\": \"Edinburgh\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edinburgh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edinburgh\"}, {\"begin\": 2508, \"end\": 2513, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999840838, \"rank\": 1.5719439931280024e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Mr Macnab\", \"from\": 2431, \"to\": 2440}, {\"ngram\": \"his family\", \"from\": 2462, \"to\": 2472}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic regatta\", \"from\": 2485, \"to\": 2504}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said: \\\"We are going to about eight races and one of them is the men's fours final.\\\"\", \"from\": 2526, \"to\": 2612, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"about eight races\", \"from\": 2552, \"to\": 2569}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's fours\", \"from\": 2589, \"to\": 2604}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His cousin Ian said: \\\"In 1924 the crew did not get time to train on the river before their first heat.\", \"from\": 2614, \"to\": 2716, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His cousin\", \"from\": 2614, \"to\": 2624}, {\"ngram\": \"Ian\", \"from\": 2625, \"to\": 2628}, {\"ngram\": \"the crew\", \"from\": 2644, \"to\": 2652}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 2665, \"to\": 2669}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 2682, \"to\": 2691}, {\"ngram\": \"their first heat\", \"from\": 2699, \"to\": 2715}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although they did not win it, they were able to do enough in various other events to get to the final.\", \"from\": 2717, \"to\": 2819, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"various other events\", \"from\": 2778, \"to\": 2798}, {\"ngram\": \"the final\", \"from\": 2809, \"to\": 2818}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"James was very keen on Leander and on rowing and carried on until he was about 65 to 70.\\\"\", \"from\": 2821, \"to\": 2911, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2822, \"end\": 2827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_VI_and_I\", \"score\": 0.9999999787078198, \"rank\": 2.1292307644688977e-08, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_VI_and_I\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/r